HEADWORD: Per diem
<hw>Per di"em</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>By the day;
substantively (chiefly U. S.), an allowance or amount of so much by the
day. Also used adjectivally; <as>as, a <ex>per diem</ex>
allowance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

